body:
Follow our job advertisements and join the exciting world of automotive industry today; come and meet the challenges and opportunities of a fast paced environment that will excite and develop you as a young professional! Delphi is willing to grow young talents into young professionals! In the same time, we have a deep knowledge to share and we need the expertise of senior professionals! Be smart and we shall use your creativity, be proactive and we shall appreciate your initiatives, be remarkable and we will definitely see you standing out from the crowd.


 Quality Engineer for Sannicolau Mare Plant 


Job Requirements:

•	Graduate Engineer of technical University;
•	Minimum of 2 year experience in the Quality field, preferably Automotive;
•	Experience in wiring harness business represents and advantage;
•	Experience and abilities in managing auditing systems and developing improvement plans;
•	Teamwork, result orientation and passionate for excellence; 
•	Basic MS Office knowledge;
•	Good knowledge of Automotive Standards: ISO TS 16949, VDA 6.3, VDA 6.5;
•	Knowledge of VW Group customer requirements is an advantage;
•	Experience in dealing with customers;
•	Strong presentation, communication, group facilitation, conflict management and training skills;
•	Experience with AIAG core tools, PPAP, APQP, MSA & SPC;
•	Analyze and troubleshoot processes for rework and scrap reduction opportunities;
•	Six Sigma certification represents an advantage;
•      Willing to travel to Sannicolau Mare (daily commute).



Main Duties and Responsibilities:

•	Continuous improvement leader of voice of process and voice of customer processes;
•	Responsible for investigating internal concerns along with external customer concerns, implementing corrective action and validating the root cause as needed;
•	Issues 8D reports and maintain Delphi Packard Resolution Tracking System; 
•	Develop and maintain the Project Quality Improvement Plan;
•	Develop and maintain the Project Control Plan;
•	Direct plant connection to CSE and customer for product quality problems;
•	Participate to Engineering Change feasibility studies and conducts System Releases;
•	Proactively investigate ways to improve the process to reduce waste, scrap and customer concerns;
•	Create Quality Alerts and customer specific Quality presentations;
•	Assist Operating System Audits, develop and maintain action plans to achieve target rating;
•	Assist Delphi Business System audits, develop and maintain action plans to achieve target rating.




If you think this is the opportunity you have been looking for, please send an application letter stating your career options and an application in English by e-mail to the following e-mail address: andrada.sitaru@delphi.com or apply on-line. All information regarding your application will be treated with the utmost confidentiality. Only selected candidates will be contacted for an interview. Delphi Packard Romania, 305600, Sannicolau Mare, Str.Garii, nr.11 tel: +40 (256)-309 300/ 0799513131 www.delphi.com
